HEADWORD: Disseizin
<hw>Dis*sei"zin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>dessaisine</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The act of
disseizing; an unlawful dispossessing and ouster of a person actually
seized of the freehold.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>disseisin</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

